Description:
Data Analyst
Job Summary:
Reporting directly to the Senior Manager, Loyalty and CRM, the CRM Data Analyst will be responsible for manipulating customer and Loyalty data from various systems (Oracle database, SQL Server, Salesforce Marketing Cloud, Loyalty platform, Google Analytics, etc.) mainly using SQL language to get customer-level insight and influence business decisions through. They will use data mining techniques, do statistical analyses, and support the team by building prediction and forecasting tools.
Key responsibilities:
Extract and manipulate data from various systems (Oracle database, SQL server, Salesforce Marketing Cloud and other Cloud Platforms, Google Analytics, Loyalty and Customer Platforms, etc.) using mainly SQL language;
Support the CRM team in A/B testing including sizing, testing strategy and results measurement:
o Support in the establishment of test measurement and sizing processes.
o Problem-solve impact sizing methodology and pull necessary data for high-level and test-specific sizing, segmentation, scaling, measurement, etc.
o Run statistical analyses for test measurement and communicate impact/learnings of weekly results (statistical significance, pre/post trend analysis, test deep-dives, ad hoc analysis, churn analysis, cohort analysis, etc.).
o Query and analyze data to inform ideation, strengthen test hypotheses, identify target segments, including sizing the impact of ideas for prioritization and understand test results.
o Propose and execute analytics to identify new and prioritized tests for the backlog.
Provide statistical analyses, build relational models, as well as prediction/forecasting models;
Support with reporting and dashboard creation to automate and track metrics and results;
Visualize output when necessary (Power BI);
Provide support on special projects and analytics as needed.
To qualify for this role, you must have...
Bachelor's degree with a focus in statistics, computer science, mathematics or related quantitative field.
2-5 years experience;
Loyalty program/CRM experience an asset;
Retail experience an asset.
SQL experience required;
Experience with statistical and data manipulation language (e.g., Python, R, SQL);
Experience working with large data sets to lead to actionable business insights;
Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite required, including advanced Excel functions;
Power BI an asset.
Bilingual (French and English);
Strong understanding of database structures;
Adept and proactive problem solver;
Strong organizational skills;
High attention to detail and commitment to high quality work;
Strong analytical and data mining skills;
Ability to work independently as well as part of a multidisciplinary team.
To be a great fit, you must...
Be able to make tough decisions;
Thrive in the face of change with a strong sense of urgency;
Challenge the status quo by contributing impactful ideas and solutions;
Build partnerships and prioritize collaboration;
Present information in an effective and concise manner;
Be proactive and exceed expected results.
On our side...
We are a global fashion retailer with the Garage and Dynamite brands at the heart of our success. With close to 300 stores in Canada and the U.S., and more than 5,000 people, we have been making our mark on fashion retail since 1975.
Our core strength is rooted in a solid understanding of our customers, while our brands continue to stand out thanks to our passionate teams who embody our values. We are proud to hire and retain aspirational leaders who are driven to achieve great things and are recognized for an entrepreneurial spirit.
What’s in it for you...
We proudly offer you a competitive salary and bonus plan, registered retirement savings, and flexible group insurance with personalized coverage that meets your needs.
As a member of our team, you’ll also enjoy our employee discount at Garage and Dynamite stores, private sample sales throughout the year and many other exciting perks, including a day off for your birthday.
Our promise…
We are committed to employment equity.
Next steps...
